        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer160428447" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7099552312215230576">Due to my busy schedule, I often read right before I go to bed. So for me, the mark of a good book is one that I pick up about half an hour before bedtime, and refuse to put down until my eyes are absolutely closing with fatigue. The Red Garden is such a book. It&apos;s magical, whimsical, powerful. Although the stories making up a patchwork history of Blackwell, MA are set in different times with (mostly) different casts of characters, you can trace the common themes and family names that wind their</span>
  <span id="freeText7099552312215230576" style="display:none">Due to my busy schedule, I often read right before I go to bed. So for me, the mark of a good book is one that I pick up about half an hour before bedtime, and refuse to put down until my eyes are absolutely closing with fatigue. The Red Garden is such a book. It's magical, whimsical, powerful. Although the stories making up a patchwork history of Blackwell, MA are set in different times with (mostly) different casts of characters, you can trace the common themes and family names that wind their way through the tales like vines. I would absolutely read it again, and recommend to discerning bookfiend friends.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7099552312215230576" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
